Robert  Egendorf (egendorf@mail.sas.upenn.edu) writes:

> I have heard of two products called SFS and SecureDrive.  What exactly are
> these? 

Programs that encrypt a disk partition on a sector basis. SFS is
implemented as a device driver and SecureDrive - as a TSR.

> Are they available for the Mac? 

No, only for the PC.

> If not, what are their Mac
> equivalents?

I am not a Mac user, but I have heard something about a product called
Curve Encrypt or something like that. However, I don't know whether
this is a disk or a file encryptor.

Regards,
Vesselin
